u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NYC-BUSINESS-BRIEF-NY     08-11 0348
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NYC-BUSINESS-BRIEF-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CABLEVISION CREATES TV AND MUSIC UNIT  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   By NICK RAVO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Cablevision Systems Corp. on Monday announced the
creation of Radio City Networks, a unit that will develop and
produce televised events and music programming. Initially, Radio
City Networks will include Radio City Television and Much Music
USA.
</P>
<P>
   Radio City Television, which is to begin next year, will
broadcast events from Radio City Music Hall, Madison Square Garden
and the Theater at Madison Square Garden, all Cablevision
properties. Much Music USA is a video music channel.
</P>
<P>
   David Kline, a senior executive with Rainbow Media, the
programming subsidiary of Cablevision, has been named president of
Radio City Networks. The job will add to his current
responsibilities, which include management of the Rainbow
Advertising Sales Corporation, the nation's largest cable
advertising representation firm.
</P>
<P>
   ``The creation of Radio City Networks marks a major step in
Rainbow's continued expansion into event and music programming,''
said Josh Sapan, president and chief executive of Rainbow Media
Holdings. ``The new unit enables us to take advantage of
opportunities presented by the additions of Radio City Music Hall
and Madison Square Garden to the Cablevision family of companies.''
</P>
<P>
   Rainbow Media's properties include the cable television networks
American Movie Classics, Romance Classics, Bravo, the Independent
Film Channel, Much Music USA, News 12 Networks, MSG Metro Channels
and Rainbow Sports, as well as a 50 percent ownership in Fox Sports
Net.
</P>
<P>
   Cablevision, based in Woodbury, N.Y., is one of the nation's
leading telecommunications and entertainment companies, and one of
the largest operators of cable television systems in the United
States. It serves more than 3.4 million cable customers with major
operations in the New York, Boston, and Cleveland metropolitan
areas.
</P>
<P>
   The company also owns a majority interest in the New York
Knicks, the New York Rangers, as well as the MSG Network.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
