   &UR; FINANCIAL &LR;  (``f'' code)
</P>
<P>
   BLACKS-BUSINESS (Undated) _ Corporate giants are chasing the
increasingly lucrative African American market. Black-owned
businesses that prospered by catering to an underserved market
during segregation-era America are gaining the attention of big
competitors seeking to sell products and services to consumers
whose needs and neighborhoods they once overlooked. By Dana Canedy.
</P>
<P>
   UNITED-HUMANA (Undated) _ United Healthcare's acquisition of
Humana, once valued at $5.5 billion, collapses because a $2.9
billion drop in the value of United Healthcare's stock last week
had sharply lessened the value of the deal to Humana shareholders.
By David J. Morrow.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-ECON (Shanghai) _ Examining the question of whether China
will devalue its currency. By Seth Faison.
