business travelers, according to a survey conducted for Crowne
Plaza Hotels. The favorite city is San Francisco, followed by New
York, Washington, and Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; ... and also number nine: &LR;  Boston ranked ninth in a Fodor's poll of
places being booked for travelers by members of the American
Society of Travel Agents. The top spot went to Orlando, followed by
Las Vegas, San Francisco, Los Angeles, New York, Seattle, San
Diego, Washington, and, after Boston, Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; Ole! &LR;  ``Muy Sabrosa,'' meaning ``Very Tasty,'' is a Southwestern
culinary celebration sponsored by the Inn on the Alameda in Santa
Fe. On various dates from November 1998 through February 1999,
Susan Curtis, a chef and founder-director of the Santa Fe School of
Cooking, will give 2 1/2-hour demonstrations. Participants also get
