<HEADLINE>
POPS FIGURES TO PERFORM AT COUNTRY INN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY MORRIS  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Boston Pops conductor Keith Lockhart will be guest pianist with
his wife, Boston Symphony Orchestra's violinist Lucia Line, and her
chamber music quartet, Innuendo, at the Seven Hill Country Inn in
Lenox, Mass. Aug. 24. The inn, a baronial mansion from the
Berkshires' glided age, hosts the Stockbridge Summer Music series
every Monday and Tuesday evening through Aug. 25. The concerts are
held in the Music Room, where Leonard Bernstein, Carly Simon, and
Beverly Sills performed as students at Tanglewood. Concert tickets
are $20; a dinner/concert package at the inn is $40. For
reservations, call 413-637-0060. Through October, the inn is also
offering Elizabethan-style Bed, Board &AMP; Bard, a midweek package
that includes accommodations, dinner, and breakfast along with a
performance by Shakespeare &AMP; Company next door at Edith Wharton's
home, The Mount. The inn, set on 27 acres, offers antique filled
rooms all with private baths, some with jet tubs and/or fireplaces.
Package prices range from $99 to $163 a person. For information,
call 800-869-6518.
</P>
