Medical help
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Virgin Atlantic has now equipped all its long-haul flights with
satellite technology to assist in the immediate diagnosis of
passenger illnesses. The MedLink emergency telemedicine services of
MedAire allows contact with board-certified emergency physicians
about any type of medical situation onboard their flight, no matter
where in the world it is. The service includes diagnoses, advice on
initial treatment, and aid in assisting the captain in deciding if
a diversion should be made. Virgin was the first airline to carry
defibrillators in the event of a heart attack onboard.
</P>
