<P>
   Advance passes for ``Van Goghs: Masterpieces from the Van Gogh
Museum, Amsterdam'' and ``Edo: The Art of Japan 1615-1868'' will be
available beginning Aug. 30 at the East Building of the National
Gallery of Art in Washington and through TicketMaster. The van Gogh
exhibit Oct. 4-Jan. 3 includes a loan of 70 paintings from the
Amsterdam museum and comprises the largest survey of the artist's
career to be seen outside the Netherlands in more than a quarter
century. Daily passes will be required for the show. For ``Edo,''
Nov. 15-Feb. 15, passes will be required on weekends, federal
holidays, and busy days during the holiday season. Free advance
passes will be available at the museum with a limit of six passes
per person. A limited number of free passes will also be available
each day for both exhibits on a first-come basis. Passes will also
be available through TicketMaster PhoneCharge for a $2.75 service
fee per pass and a $1.25 handling fee per order. Call 800-551-SEAT
outside Washington, Baltimore, and northern Virginia. For pass
information on ``Van Gogh,'' call 202-737-4215; for ``Edo,'' call
202-789-4999. The gallery's Web site is www.nga.gov.
