<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SCIENCE-NYT-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Science and health stories in sight at this hour from The New
York Times News Service for  &UR; WEDNESDAY &LR; , Aug. 12:
</P>
<P>
   SCI-BALLOON-FOSSETT (Undated) _ Speeding along at more than 100
miles an hour, millionaire adventurer Steve Fossett on Tuesday
became the first balloonist to cross the South Atlantic Ocean. As
he passed the southern tip of Africa on his way eastward from
Argentina he passed the 5,000-mile mark _ one fifth of the distance
he will cover if he succeeds in becoming the first balloonist to
circle the world non-stop. Fossett began his journey last Friday
from Mendoza, Argentina, in his quest for ballooning glory and a
$1-million prize. By Malcolm W. Browne.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867. And be sure to look for other science stories from our
partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst Newspapers, The Houston Chronicle, The Arizona Republic,
Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News,
San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
