<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THEORIES ON HOW THE TERM `IVY LEAGUE' SPROUTED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Does the Roman numeral IV have any significance with the
naming of the Ivy League?
</P>
<P>
   _ G.B., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: According to the Information Please Sports Almanac and other
sources, the term ``Ivy League'' was coined by a New York
Herald-Tribune sportswriter in the 1930s.
</P>
<P>
   The name was inspired by ivy-covered walls at member schools:
Brown, Columbia, Cornell, Dartmouth, Harvard, Penn, Princeton and
Yale.
</P>
<P>
   There's unsubstantiated speculation that Columbia, Harvard,
Princeton and Yale were dubbed the ``IV league'' in the late 1800s
after forming a four-member football association.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sometimes Columbia is replaced by Penn in the telling,''
Margaret Smagorinsky writes in a 1993 Princeton historical
publication. ``This is interesting, if true, but why did it take
over 100 years to enter into Princeton's history?''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Matt Damon was my student in 1983 when I was teaching
language arts in Cambridge, Mass. He was very bright and talented.
Where can I write to tell him how proud I am to have known him?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.T., Teaneck, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Damon in care of Creative Artists Agency, 9830
Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   The actor, who turns 28 on Oct. 8, is currently appearing in
``Saving Private Ryan.'' Later this year he'll be reteaming with
Ben Affleck for ``Dogma'' and with Edward Norton in ``Rounders.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to the golfer Gary Player?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.R.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write in care of the Gary Player Group, 3930 RCA Boulevard,
Suite 3001, Palm Beach Gardens, FL 33410.
</P>
<P>
   The Player Group has a World Wide Web site at www.garyplayer.com
featuring tournament news, his golf course designs, and vacation
tours of South African courses.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
