<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Study reveals that chlamydia affects one in three sexually
active teen girls
 &HT;    By Patricia Guthrie
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Chlamydia, already considered a severe, silent sexually
transmitted disease among adult women, is striking earlier and more
frequently, a new study of teenage girls shows.
</P>
<P>
   Almost one in three sexually active adolescent girls between
ages 12 and 19 in the Baltimore area tested positive for the
