<P>
   (NYT21) UNDATED -- Aug. 11, 1998 -- BELARUS-ECON, 8-11 --
Belarus' ruble, called the zaichik, or little hare, has lost half
of its worth in five months and more than 10 percent in the last
week alone. Now, the government has announced a new and perhaps
unintentionally revealing plan to shore up the ruble's value:
starting next week, the country will no longer accept its own
currency as payment for exports. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
