8-11 -- Mamasa Njie, left, and a partner, Joseph Natal, working on
an analysis of pond water at Camp Vacamas during their three-week
session combining camp with school work. ``I thought we were just
coming here and we'd pick what we wanted to do, like in other
camps,'' Mamasa says. (Richard Harbus/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) OGDENSBURG, N.Y. -- Aug. 11, 1998 --
CANADA-BORDER-SHOPPING-2, 8-11 -- The empty Park Plaza in
Ogdensburg, a town in the North Country where Canadians shoppers
were plentiful before the currency woes. Lou Williams, the owner of
two Ogdensburg motels, says the Canadians used to arrive on Friday,
``party hearty all night and spend all day Saturday shopping.''
Then ``they'd shop a little more on Sunday and go home.'' (Michael
J. Okoniewski/New York Times Photo)
</P>
