that reach only so far. In the areas that get little relief from
the drought, the cotton bolls are stunted. While many parts of the
country, including the Northeast, are suffering through dry months
verging on drought, the situation is particularly severe in Texas
and Oklahoma. (David Bowser/New York Times Photo)
