<P>
   (NYT15) HOUSTON -- Aug. 11, 1998 -- SOUTHWEST-DROUGHT-1, 8-11 --
Lynn Bartlett, a farmer in Texas, has sprinklers for his cotton
that reach only so far. His irrigated, tall cotton is behind him.
``This is basically burnt-up cotton,'' he says. ``We had a good
planting rain back in May, then a week or so later the tap just
shut off and it's been off ever since.'' (David Bowser/New York
Times Photo) *LITE
