<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-SOUTHWEST-DROUGHT-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``My dairy farmers tell me that because of the heat the cows are
just off their feed, off their milk and production is down a third
or a half. I know how the cows feel.''
</P>
<P>
   _DENNIS HOWARD, Oklahoma's agriculture commissioner.
</P>
</TEXT>
