value of the Canadian dollar. It is as if half the people around
here had suddenly moved away. Along almost all of the U.S.-Canada
border, the Canadian side is much more populous, and shopping by
Canadians, who were drawn across the border by lower sales taxes,
longer shopping hours and often more choices, had formed an
important part of local markets on the U.S. side. By Iver Peterson.
WITH PHOTOS (NYT18,19)
