<SLUG> BC-TEN-ACUNOTE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WIMBLEDON FINAL REJUVENATES TAUZIAT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE STEVENS  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANHATTAN BEACH, Calif. _ Nathalie Tauziat doesn't mind when an
entire country's hopes fall on her. ``Every time I play, I play for
France and for myself,'' she said. ``It does not put extra pressure
on me.''
</P>
<P>
   So this year, when Tauziat became the first Frenchwoman since
Suzanne Lenglen in 1925 to play in the Wimbledon final, it did not
faze her. She lost to Jana Novotna, but she remains a fan favorite
in France.
</P>
<P>
   Her showing at Wimbledon brought her the most attention of her
career, even though she has been on the women's tour for 15 years
and was ranked as high as 11th in 1992.
</P>
<P>
   Tauziat, ranked 13th, continues to work off her June success at
Wimbledon. She beat Chanda Rubin 6-4, 7-5 on Tuesday to advance in
the Acura Classic, where she will meet doubles partner and fellow
countrywoman Alexandra Fusai today in the second round. Though
Tauziat might be more recognizable since Wimbledon, the resident of
Bayonne, France, said she is ``still the same person.''
</P>
<P>
   Tauziat, 30, is the oldest player here who did not play
qualifying matches. As No. 5, she is the highest-seeded player to
have played thus far at Manhattan Beach.
</P>
<P>
   __ Back-to-back parties?: Iva Majoli turned 21 on Tuesday and
she celebrated with friends in Santa Monica at night. It helped
that she posted a 1-6, 6-2, 6-4 win over Rita Grande earlier.
</P>
<P>
   Now 20th-ranked Majoli will meet top-seeded Martina Hingis today
in the second round, hoping for an upset. Said Majoli, ``If I win,
I'm sure I'm going to have another party.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Venus withdraws, again: Venus Williams, who has tendinitis in
her left knee, has withdrawn from the tournament. She had planned
to play doubles with her sister, Serena, but is dropping out of a
second straight event. Last week at the Toshiba Classic in La
Costa, Williams withdrew during a quarterfinal match against Mary
Pierce while trailing 4-0 in the third set.
</P>
<P>
   __ Stars in action: The match between top-seeded Hingis and
Majoli should be the highlight of today's action. Third-seeded
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario plays Ai Sugiyama, and fourth-seeded Monica
Seles meets Barbara Paulus.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
